      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e If it didn\u0027t have one, we should have returned false searching for DT_SONAME above. If we get this far, then we should be able to expect that offset points to a valid string.\n\nI guess that’s true, in a sense.\n\nBut this is entirely in the control of the module and how well (or badly) it’s linked, or modified after linking, or even hand-crafted. While we definitely want to detect things that we don’t understand and things that don’t make any sense (like this), I’m not sure we should be exposing ourselves to a DCHECK when we encounter someone else’s malformatted garbage.\n\nLike I said, we do want to detect this kind of condition, but this seems more like a thing that we’d LOG(WARNING) for (here, LOG_IF would be an easy drop-in for DCHECK). That has the benefit of surviving even in release builds, so if this does wind up happening a lot, we’ll collect some evidence of it in logs from the field.",
